</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>AB2520:v99#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="AB2520"/><meta name="dc:title" content="AB &#xA;              2520-&#xA;                INTRODUCED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 2520</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Krell<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 20, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to amend Section 1799.1 of the Civil Code, relating to civil law. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 2520, as introduced, Krell.
                          Business records: disclosure.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law prohibits a business entity that performs bookkeeping services from disclosing the contents of any record that is prepared or maintained by the business entity to any person, other than the individual or business entity that is the subject of the record, without express written consent, except as specified.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would make nonsubstantive changes to the provision described above that prohibits business entities that perform bookkeeping services from making certain disclosures.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.49093517066526615"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Section 1799.1 of the Civil Code is amended to read:</div><div><div id="id_9DDF396B-CD30-4635-B341-9F497BA3492B"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">1799.1.</h6> (a) No business entity<font color="#B30000"><strike> which</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> that</i></font> performs bookkeeping services shall disclose in whole or in part the contents of any record, including the disclosure of information in the record in any composite of<font color="#B30000"><strike> information, which</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> information that</i></font> is prepared or maintained by<font color="#B30000"><strike> such</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> the</i></font>
				  business entity to any<font color="#B30000"><strike> person,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> person</i></font> other than the individual or business entity<font color="#B30000"><strike> which</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> that</i></font> is the subject of the record, without the express written consent of<font color="#B30000"><strike> such</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> the</i></font> individual or business entity.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) This section shall not apply to the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) To a disclosure to any person pursuant to a
				  subpoena or court order.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) To a disclosure<font color="#B30000"><strike> which</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
				  that</i></font> is discoverable.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) To a disclosure to any person acting pursuant to a lawful search warrant.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4) To a disclosure to a law enforcement agency<font color="#B30000"><strike> when</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> if</i></font> required for investigations of criminal activity, unless<font color="#B30000"><strike> such</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> the</i></font> disclosure is prohibited by law.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(5) To a disclosure to a taxing agency for purposes of tax administration.</div></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
